provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: saved_custom_table
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, saved_report_id
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_usage_custom_tables filters
saved_custom_table.display_name,
saved_custom_table.row_group_by,
saved_custom_table.column_group_by,
saved_custom_table.group_by_tag (+2 more)
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
The generated runtime reuses an existing custom
table by listing on the required compartmentId
and savedReportId request scope, then matching
the returned savedCustomTable payload on
displayName and any populated row, column, tag,
depth, or version fields.
The SDK surface does not expose lifecycle states
on CustomTable bodies, so create and update
settle through read-after-write GetCustomTable
confirmation instead of lifecycle polling; a
service-local wrapper converts that confirmed
reread into settled Active status.
In-place updates are limited to
savedCustomTable; compartmentId and
savedReportId require replacement and are
rejected before OCI mutation.
Delete retains the finalizer until
GetCustomTable confirms the custom table no
longer exists.
end note
